        "description": "Flatten all circle parameters into a single vector [x0,y0,r0,x1,y1,r1,...]. Define constraint functions: (1) circle-wall constraints: r_i \u2264 x_i \u2264 1-r_i and r_i \u2264 y_i \u2264 1-r_i, (2) non-overlap constraints: ||c_i - c_j|| \u2265 r_i + r_j for all pairs i<j. Use SLSQP method which handles nonlinear constraints. Start from the current hexagonal pattern as initial guess. The optimizer will adjust both positions and radii simultaneously to maximize sum while respecting all geometric constraints.",
        "what_to_optimize": "Maximize sum of radii by jointly optimizing positions and radii under geometric constraints",
        "cautions": "SLSQP requires constraints as callable functions returning values \u2264 0 for feasible points. Use multiple restarts from perturbed initial positions. Set ftol and maxiter appropriately. The non-overlap constraints are non-convex so multiple initializations help avoid local minima.",
