        "description": "Initialize circle centers, then iterate: (1) Compute Voronoi diagram of current centers, (2) For each cell, the maximum inscribed circle radius equals the minimum distance from site to any Voronoi edge or square boundary, (3) Move each center slightly toward its Voronoi cell centroid to improve packing, (4) Repeat until convergence. This geometric approach naturally maximizes radii by pushing circles apart. The Voronoi edges define the 'natural' neighbors for each circle.",
        "what_to_optimize": "Geometric positioning that maximizes each circle's local available space through Voronoi-based analysis",
        "cautions": "Handle Voronoi cells that extend outside the unit square by clipping to boundaries. Some cells may be unbounded - clip to square. The iteration should use small step sizes to avoid oscillation. This is a fixed-point iteration, not gradient-based optimization.",
